    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Compiling UnrealIRCD on an iPod touch 2G]]></title>
    <link href="http://transfusion.github.io/blog/2013/06/11/compiling-unrealircd-on-an-ipod-touch-2g/"/>
    <updated>2013-06-11T12:49:00+04:00</updated>
    <id>http://transfusion.github.io/blog/2013/06/11/compiling-unrealircd-on-an-ipod-touch-2g</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>A picture to prove success just so you&rsquo;ll read on ))</p>

<p><a href="#" data-reveal-id="image-link"><img src="http://i41.tinypic.com/2013k6.png"/ alt="UnrealIRCD in MobileTerminal on iPod Touch 4.2.1"></a></p>

<div id="image-link" class="reveal-modal">
  <img src="http://oi43.tinypic.com/f0zupg.jpg" alt="UnrealIRCD in MobileTerminal on iPod Touch 4.2.1"></a>
</div>




<!-- more -->


<p><a href="#" data-reveal-id="image-link-modal2"><img src="http://oi43.tinypic.com/k00qwm.jpg"/ alt="uname -a"></a></p>

<div id="image-link-modal2" class="reveal-modal">
  <img src="http://oi42.tinypic.com/qp5pj5.jpg" alt="uname -a"></a>
</div>


<h1>Prerequisites</h1>

<ul>
<li>openssl (I have version 0.9.8k-9 from Cydia)</li>
<li>iphone-gcc (follow this guide: <a href="http://code.google.com/p/iphone-gcc-full/">http://code.google.com/p/iphone-gcc-full/</a>)</li>
<li>libgcc (follow this guide: <a href="http://code.google.com/p/iphone-gcc-full/">http://code.google.com/p/iphone-gcc-full/</a>)</li>
<li>libz.dylib / zlib (If you can&rsquo;t be bothered to get this from the iPhone SDK <a href="http://cydia.radare.org/debs/">http://cydia.radare.org/debs/</a> works too)</li>
<li>wget (who doesn&rsquo;t need wget)</li>
</ul>


<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>wget "http://www.unrealircd.com/downloads/Unreal3.2.10.1.tar.gz" | tar -xvzf -</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h1>Configuring</h1>

<p>For some reason I had to run the ./configure as root after cd&#8217;ing into the directory where I extracted the files as the mobile user; perhaps due to an inability to run unsigned applications?</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>checking whether we are cross compiling... configure: error: in `/var/mobile/Unreal3.2.10.1':
</span><span class='line'>configure: error: cannot run C compiled programs.
</span><span class='line'>If you meant to cross compile, use `--host'.</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>After running as root, everything went rather smoothly. Edit dpath and spath as you wish.</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>./configure --with-showlistmodes --enable-ssl --enable-ziplinks --enable-inet6 --with-listen=5 --with-dpath=/var/mobile/UnrealIRCD-build --with-spath=/var/mobile/UnrealIRCD-build/src/ircd --with-nick-history=2000 --with-sendq=3000000 --with-bufferpool=18 --with-permissions=0600 --with-fd-setsize=1024 --enable-dynamic-linking</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>I forgot to use &lsquo;time&rsquo; but estimate it perhaps took around 20 minutes.</p>

<p>After make &amp;&amp; make install:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>openssl req -new -key server.key -out server.csr
</span><span class='line'>openssl x509 -req -days 365 -in server.csr -signkey server.key -out server.crt
</span><span class='line'>cp server.key server.key.pem
</span><span class='line'>cp server.crt server.cert.pem</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>to generate the certificate and key needed for the SSL connection.</p>

<p>After running ./unreal start ; it required some source modules in the build folder and the config file for the IRCD.</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>cp -r /var/mobile/Unreal3.2.10.1/src/ ../UnrealIRCD-build/
</span><span class='line'>cp /var/mobile/UnrealIRCD-build/src/example.conf /var/mobile/UnrealIRCD-build/unrealircd.conf</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Edit the config file as you wish!&hellip;</p>
]]></content>
